<concept id="id" class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Create your first <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/> plugin</title><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><p class="- topic/p ">This tutorial will walk you through creating your first <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/> plugin. The plugin in this tutorial does two things:</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li ">Listens to the <xref format="html" href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/katalon-studio-platform/blob/master/com.katalon.platform/src/main/java/com/katalon/platform/api/extension/PluginActivationListener.java" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">plugin
               activation event</xref> then prints a hello message after the plugin
            was installed successfully in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/>.</li><li class="- topic/li ">Listens to the <xref format="html" href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/katalon-studio-platform/blob/master/com.katalon.platform/src/main/java/com/katalon/platform/api/extension/EventListenerInitializer.java" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">test
               execution event</xref> then prints a report message in Console.</li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">You can find the source code of this tutorial <xref format="html" href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/katalon-studio-sample-plugin" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">here</xref>.</p><p class="- topic/p ">A <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/> plugin is a Maven-based Java project, and also
         an <xref format="html" href="http://spring.io/blog/2008/02/18/creating-osgi-bundles/" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">OSGI
            bundle 1</xref> project. A plugin contains these components:</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li ">The <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">pom.xml</codeph> to describe your plugin, what it is
            (name, version, vendor,etc).</li><li class="- topic/li ">The <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">plugin.xml</codeph> to let Katalon Studio know about
            all the extensions of your plugin.</li><li class="- topic/li ">All packaged codes of your plugin.</li></ul><section class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Requirements</title><p class="- topic/p "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li ">Java SDK 1.8</li><li class="- topic/li ">Maven 3.3+</li><li class="- topic/li ">Download <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/> version 6.0.3 (beta): <xref format="html" href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/katalon/release-beta/6.0.3/Katalon_Studio_Windows_32.zip" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">win32</xref>,
            <xref format="html" href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/katalon/release-beta/6.0.3/Katalon_Studio_Windows_64.zip" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">win64</xref>,
            <xref format="html" href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/katalon/release-beta/6.0.3/Katalon+Studio.dmg" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">macOS</xref>,
            and <xref format="html" href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/katalon/release-beta/6.0.3/Katalon_Studio_Linux_64.tar.gz" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">linux64</xref>.</li></ol></p></section></conbody></concept>